        contentMd: "# Anxiety Disorders - Foundation\n\n## Definition\nAnxiety disorders: Mental health conditions characterized by excessive worry, fear, or anxiety affecting daily functioning.\n\n## Classification (DSM-5)\n**Generalized Anxiety Disorder (GAD)**: Persistent, excessive worry\n**Panic Disorder**: Recurrent panic attacks + anticipatory anxiety\n**Social Anxiety Disorder (SAD)**: Fear of social situations\n**Specific Phobia**: Fear of particular object/situation\n**Agoraphobia**: Fear of places/situations where escape is difficult\n**Separation Anxiety Disorder**: Fear of separation in children\n**Selective Mutism**: Failure to speak in some situations\n\n## Epidemiology in India\n**Prevalence**: 7-12% lifetime prevalence\n**Age of onset**: Usually 15-35 years\n**Gender**: More common in females (2:1 ratio)\n**Comorbidity**: Often with depression (60%)\n**Impact**: Significant functional impairment\n\n## Risk Factors\n**Genetic**: Family history of anxiety/depression\n**Environmental**: Trauma, stress, life events\n**Biological**: Neurotransmitter abnormalities\n**Personality**: Neuroticism, perfectionism\n**Medical**: Thyroid disease, cardiopulmonary conditions",
