        estimatedMinutes: 30,
        summary: "Neurobiology and pathophysiology of anxiety",
        contentMd: "# Anxiety Disorders - Mechanism\n\n## Neurotransmitter Hypothesis\n**GABA**: Main inhibitory neurotransmitter, reduced in anxiety\n**Serotonin (5-HT)**: Mood regulation, reduced in anxiety\n**Norepinephrine**: Arousal, excessive in anxiety\n**Dopamine**: Reward/motivation, dysregulated\n**Glutamate**: Excitatory, excessive in anxiety\n\n## Brain Regions Involved\n**Amygdala**: Fear processing, hyperactive in anxiety\n**Anterior cingulate**: Error detection, overactive\n**Prefrontal cortex (PFC)**: Emotion regulation, underactive\n**Insula**: Interoceptive awareness, hyperactive\n**Hippocampus**: Memory, reduced volume in PTSD\n\n## Stress Response System (HPA Axis)\n**Hypothalamus**: Releases CRH\n**Pituitary**: Releases ACTH\n**Adrenal**: Releases cortisol\n**Dysregulation**: Hyperactivity or hypoactivity\n**Feedback loop**: Impaired cortisol suppression\n\n## Fear Conditioning and Extinction\n**Fear acquisition**: Amygdala-mediated learning\n**Fear extinction**: PFC-mediated extinction learning\n**Impairment**: Poor extinction in anxiety (hyperactive amygdala, hypoactive PFC)\n**Neural basis**: Reduced GABAergic inhibition\n\n## Genetic Factors\n**Heritability**: 30-40% for anxiety disorders\n**COMT gene**: Catechol-O-methyltransferase (dopamine metabolism)\n**Serotonin transporter (5-HTTLPR)**: S allele associated with increased anxiety\n**BDNF**: Brain-derived neurotrophic factor (neuroplasticity)\n\n## Cognitive Models\n**Threat appraisal**: Overestimation of threat\n**Avoidance**: Maintains anxiety through negative reinforcement\n**Worry**: Cognitive avoidance strategy\n**Hypervigilance**: Selective attention to threats\n\n## Neuroinflammation\n**Cytokines**: IL-6, TNF-alpha elevated\n**Microglial activation**: Neuroinflammatory response\n**BBB permeability**: Increased in anxiety\n**Implications**: Anti-inflammatory treatments being explored",
