        estimatedMinutes: 20,
        summary: "Clinical presentation, diagnosis, and treatment",
        contentMd: "# Anxiety Disorders - Clinical\n\n## GAD Clinical Features\n**Core symptom**: Excessive worry >6 months\n**Physical**: Muscle tension, restlessness, fatigue\n**Cognitive**: Difficulty concentrating, mind blanking\n**Associated**: Sleep disturbance, irritability\n**Onset**: Usually 20-40 years\n\n## Panic Disorder\n**Panic attack**: Sudden intense fear + physical symptoms (10-20 min)\n**Symptoms**: Chest pain, dyspnea, palpitations, dizziness, fear of death/losing control\n**Agoraphobia**: Often develops after panic attacks\n**Frequency**: Recurrent attacks with >1 month anticipatory anxiety\n\n## Social Anxiety Disorder\n**Fear**: Social situations where evaluated by others\n**Symptoms**: Blushing, trembling, sweating, difficulty speaking\n**Avoidance**: School, work, dating\n**Physical**: Tension, racing heart in social settings\n**Onset**: Usually adolescence\n\n## Assessment\n**Clinical interview**: Detailed history, triggers, avoidance\n**GAD-7 scale**: 7-item self-report (0-21 score)\n**STAI**: State-Trait Anxiety Inventory\n**Vital signs**: Tachycardia, elevated BP during assessment\n**Medical workup**: TSH, cardiac evaluation if warranted\n\n## Psychological Treatment (First-Line)\n**Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)**:\n  - Cognitive restructuring (challenging catastrophic thoughts)\n  - Exposure/Behavioral experiments\n  - Problem-solving training\n  - Relaxation techniques\n  - Effectiveness: 60-70% response rate\n\n**Mindfulness-Based Interventions**:\n  - Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT)\n  - Mindfulness-Based Stress Reduction (MBSR)\n  - Meta-cognitive therapy\n\n## Pharmacological Treatment\n**SSRIs** (first-line):\n  - Sertraline 50-100 mg daily\n  - Escitalopram 10-20 mg daily\n  - Paroxetine 20-40 mg daily\n  - Venlafaxine (SNRI) 75-225 mg daily\n  - Efficacy: 60-70%\n\n**Benzodiazepines** (short-term only):\n  - Lorazepam, clonazepam for acute anxiety\n  - Avoid long-term (dependence risk)\n  - Maximum 2-4 weeks\n\n**Other agents**:\n  - Buspirone (anxiolytic, no dependence)\n  - Hydroxyzine (antihistamine)\n  - Beta-blockers (physical symptoms)\n  - Pregabalin (GAD-approved)\n\n## Combined Treatment\n**CBT + SSRI**: Superior to either alone\n**Timeline**: 4-6 weeks for SSRI efficacy\n**Monitoring**: Suicidality especially in young (<25 years)\n**Maintenance**: Continue 6-12 months minimum\n\n## Lifestyle Interventions\n**Exercise**: Reduces anxiety, improves mood\n**Sleep hygiene**: Essential for anxiety control\n**Caffeine/alcohol reduction**: Improve anxiety\n**Stress management**: Meditation, yoga, breathing\n**Social support**: Important protective factor",
