        contentMd: "# Blood: Composition & Functions - Foundation\n\n## Blood Composition\n**Volume**: ~5-6 L in adults\n**Plasma**: 55% (~3 L), contains proteins, electrolytes, glucose\n**Formed elements**: 45% (~2.5 L), cells and platelets\n\n## Plasma Proteins (7-9 g/dL)\n**Albumin**: 50-60%, osmotic function, transport\n**Globulins**: 20-30%, immune function (antibodies)\n**Fibrinogen**: 3-4%, coagulation\n**Clotting factors**: II, V, VII, VIII, IX, X, XI, XII, XIII\n\n## Formed Elements\n**RBCs**: 4.5-5.5 million/μL (males), 4-5 million/μL (females)\n**WBCs**: 4,500-11,000/μL (normal)\n**Platelets**: 150,000-400,000/μL\n**Lifespan**: RBC 120 days, WBC variable, Platelets 7-10 days\n\n## Functions of Blood\n**Transport**: Oxygen, CO2, nutrients, hormones\n**Thermoregulation**: Heat distribution\n**pH buffering**: Maintains acid-base balance\n**Immunity**: WBCs, antibodies\n**Hemostasis**: Platelets, coagulation factors\n**Hormone delivery**: Endocrine signaling",
