        contentMd: "# Blood Composition & Functions - Mechanism\n\n## Hemoglobin Structure and Function\n**Structure**: 4 globin chains (2 alpha, 2 beta), 4 heme groups\n**Oxygen binding**: Cooperative binding (sigmoidal curve)\n**P50**: 26-27 mmHg (oxygen tension at 50% saturation)\n**CO2 transport**: Carbaminohemoglobin (23%)\n**pH buffering**: Bicarbonate buffer system\n\n## RBC Production (Erythropoiesis)\n**Location**: Bone marrow (red marrow)\n**Stimulation**: Erythropoietin (EPO) in response to hypoxia\n**Timeline**: 7-10 days from proerythroblast to mature RBC\n**Stages**: Proerythroblast → Early/Intermediate/Late erythroblasts → Reticulocyte → RBC\n**Iron requirement**: ~25-30 mg/day\n**Folate/B12 requirement**: DNA synthesis\n\n## WBC Types and Functions\n**Neutrophils** (50-70%): Phagocytosis, inflammatory response\n**Lymphocytes** (20-40%): Adaptive immunity (T, B, NK cells)\n**Monocytes** (2-8%): Phagocytosis, antigen presentation\n**Eosinophils** (1-4%): Parasitic infections, allergies\n**Basophils** (<1%): Mast cell equivalent, histamine release\n\n## WBC Production (Leukopoiesis)\n**Location**: Bone marrow\n**Timeline**: Neutrophils 7-10 days, lymphocytes weeks\n**Granulocytes**: Myeloid lineage (G-CSF, GM-CSF stimulation)\n**Lymphocytes**: Lymphoid lineage (IL-7 stimulation)\n**Pool distribution**: Marginal pool (~2/3) vs circulating (~1/3)\n\n## Platelet Formation (Megakaryopoiesis)\n**Location**: Bone marrow megakaryocytes\n**Timeline**: 10 days from hematopoietic stem cell\n**Formation**: Megakaryocyte cytoplasmic fragmentation\n**TPO stimulation**: Thrombopoietin regulates production\n**Reserve pool**: 30-40% in spleen\n\n## Hemostasis (Three Components)\n**1. Vascular phase** (seconds): Vasoconstriction, Weibel-Palade body release\n**2. Platelet phase** (1-5 min): Adhesion, activation, aggregation\n**3. Coagulation phase** (minutes): Cascade of clotting factors → fibrin clot\n\n## Coagulation Cascade\n**Intrinsic pathway**: XII→XI→IX (with VIII) → X\n**Extrinsic pathway**: Tissue factor + VII → X\n**Common pathway**: X→II (with V) → I (fibrinogen→fibrin)\n**Anticoagulation**: Protein C, Protein S, antithrombin\n\n## Fibrinolysis\n**tPA (tissue plasminogen activator)**: Converts plasminogen → plasmin\n**Plasmin**: Degrades fibrin clot\n**Regulation**: Alpha-2-plasmin inhibitor, PAI-1\n**Timeline**: Hours to days for clot lysis",
