        summary: "Clinical assessment and pathology of blood",
        contentMd: "# Blood Composition & Functions - Clinical\n\n## Complete Blood Count (CBC) Interpretation\n**Hemoglobin**: 13-16 g/dL males, 12-15 g/dL females\n**Hematocrit**: 38-50% males, 35-45% females\n**RBC count**: 4.5-5.5 million/μL males, 4-5 million/μL females\n**MCV** (mean corpuscular volume): 80-100 fL\n**Reticulocyte count**: 0.5-2% (new RBCs)\n\n**WBC differential**:\n  - Neutrophils: 50-70%\n  - Lymphocytes: 20-40%\n  - Monocytes: 2-8%\n  - Eosinophils: 1-4%\n  - Basophils: <1%\n\n**Platelet count**: 150,000-400,000/μL\n**Platelet morphology**: Normal 6-10 μm size\n\n## Clinical Assessment of Blood Function\n**Anemia**: Hemoglobin <13 g/dL males, <12 g/dL females\n**Classification**:\n  - **Microcytic** (MCV <80): Iron deficiency, thalassemia\n  - **Normocytic** (MCV 80-100): Acute bleeding, hemolysis, bone marrow failure\n  - **Macrocytic** (MCV >100): B12/folate deficiency, reticulocytosis\n\n**Polycythemia**: Hemoglobin >16 g/dL males, >15 g/dL females\n  - **Relative**: Dehydration\n  - **Absolute**: Bone marrow disorder or hypoxia\n\n**Leukopenia**: WBC <4,500/μL\n  - **Neutropenia**: Risk of infection\n  - **Lymphopenia**: Immune compromise\n  - **Monocytopenia**: Reduced monocyte-mediated immunity\n\n**Leukocytosis**: WBC >11,000/μL\n  - **Infection**: Bacterial, viral, fungal\n  - **Leukemia**: Malignant proliferation\n  - **Stress/exercise**: Temporary elevation\n\n**Thrombocytopenia**: <150,000/μL\n  - **Immune**: ITP, drug-induced\n  - **Non-immune**: TTP, DIC, HUS\n  - **Decreased production**: Bone marrow failure\n\n## Coagulation Disorders\n**PT (prothrombin time)**: Extrinsic + common pathway (normal 12-14 sec)\n**aPTT (activated partial thromboplastin time)**: Intrinsic + common (normal 25-35 sec)\n**Bleeding time**: Platelet function (normal <10 min)\n**Thrombin time**: Fibrinogen level (normal 14-20 sec)\n\n**Bleeding disorders**:\n  - **Hemophilia A/B**: Factor deficiency, prolonged aPTT\n  - **von Willebrand disease**: Platelet dysfunction + factor deficiency\n  - **DIC**: Consumption coagulopathy (low Plt, Fib, high PT/aPTT)\n\n## Transfusion Management\n**RBC transfusion**: Hemoglobin <7 g/dL (or >8-9 in symptomatic)\n**Platelet transfusion**: <10,000 (or <20,000 if fever/infection)\n**FFP**: Coagulation factor replacement\n**Cryoprecipitate**: Fibrinogen replacement\n**Compatibility**: ABO type, Rh status critical",
