        contentMd: "# Blood Composition & Functions - Exam Prep\n\n## Normal Blood Values (High-Yield)\n| Parameter | Normal Range |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| Hemoglobin | 13-16 g/dL (M), 12-15 (F) |\n| Hematocrit | 38-50% (M), 35-45% (F) |\n| RBC | 4.5-5.5M/μL (M), 4-5M (F) |\n| WBC | 4.5-11K/μL |\n| Platelets | 150-400K/μL |\n| MCV | 80-100 fL |\n| Reticulocytes | 0.5-2% |\n\n## RBC Lifespan and Destruction\n**Lifespan**: 120 days\n**Site**: Bone marrow (90%), spleen (10%)\n**Bilirubin**: From heme degradation (normal 0.3-1.2 mg/dL)\n**Haptoglobin**: Binds free Hb (normal 30-200 mg/dL)\n**Hemosiderin**: Iron storage form\n\n## Hemoglobin Variants\n**HbA**: 95% (normal adult)\n**HbA2**: 2% (normal)\n**HbF**: <1% (normal, increased in thalassemia major)\n**HbS**: Sickle cell\n**HbC**: C disease\n\n## Anemia Red Flags\n- Hemoglobin <7 g/dL (critical)\n- Rapid drop in Hb (acute bleeding)\n- Reticulocyte count <2% with anemia (bone marrow failure)\n- Elevated retic count (hemolysis, bleeding, response to treatment)\n\n## WBC Differential Interpretation\n**Left shift**: Increased immature neutrophils (infection, leukemia)\n**Right shift**: Hypersegmented neutrophils (B12/folate deficiency)\n**Lymphocytosis**: Viral infection, CLL\n**Eosinophilia**: Parasites, allergies, leukemia\n**Monocytosis**: TB, histoplasmosis, leukemia\n\n## Coagulation Profile Patterns\n**Prolonged PT only**: Factor VII deficiency, warfarin\n**Prolonged aPTT only**: Factor VIII/IX/XI deficiency, lupus anticoagulant\n**Prolonged PT + aPTT**: Factor II/V/X deficiency, DIC, liver disease\n**Normal PT/aPTT + bleeding**: Platelet disorder, vWF deficiency\n\n## Reticulocyte Count Interpretation\n**Low with anemia**: Bone marrow failure\n**High with anemia**: Hemolysis, acute bleeding (appropriate response)\n**High with normal Hb**: Polycythemia vera, smoking (compensation)\n\n## Blood Groups and Transfusion\n**ABO**: A, B, AB, O (universal donor O-, recipient AB+)\n**Rh**: Positive or negative\n**Rare blood groups**: Duffy, Kidd, MNS (clinically relevant)\n**Cross-matching**: Ensures compatibility\n\n## Critical Values Requiring Action\n- **Hemoglobin**: <5 or >20 g/dL\n- **Hematocrit**: <15 or >60%\n- **WBC**: <2.5 or >30K/μL\n- **Platelets**: <20 or >1000K/μL\n- **PT/INR**: >4.0 (high bleeding risk)",
